# Security routing (canonical)

Replaces the always-on `vulnerability-scanner.mdc` prose duplicate. Load skills by task; use subagents for deep review.

## Quick script

```bash
python scripts/security_scan.py <project_path>
```

Reference checklists: `checklists.md` (OWASP Top 10, Auth, API, Data protection).

## Skill routing

| Task | Load |
|------|------|
| PR/diff security review | `common/common-code-review` + subagent `security-reviewer` |
| OWASP checklist / web+API review | `common/common-owasp` |
| Secrets, injection surfaces, audit scan | `common/common-security-audit` |
| Auth/crypto/input validation standards | `common/common-security-standards` |
| TypeScript-specific hardening | `typescript/typescript-security` |
| React client security | `react/react-security` |

## Subagent routing

- PR/diff and deep review: `security-reviewer` (compliance mode for SOC2/ISO/program audits)

## Core principles (keep in every security task)

- Assume breach; least privilege; fail-closed on auth/authz errors.
- Map attack surface before scanning; prioritize by exploitability × asset value.
- No finding without reproduction path and remediation.
